ffmpeg (6:1.0.1-0ubuntu0andya) quantal; urgency=medium

  * Update to 1.0.1

 -- Andy Armstrong <andy@hexten.net>  Mon, 17 Dec 2012 19:44:36 +0000

ffmpeg (6:0.10.6-0ubuntu0jon1) quantal; urgency=medium

  * Merge from debian, no remaining changes
  * Build against libtiff5-dev instead of libtiff4-dev if available

 -- Jon Severinsson <jon@severinsson.net>  Mon, 12 Nov 2012 12:15:00 +0100

ffmpeg (6:0.10.6-0jon1) wheezy; urgency=medium

  * Imported Upstream version 0.10.6
  * Merge from debian, remaining changes:
    - Package ffmpeg rather than libav
    - Remove libav specific debian patch
    - Add libswresample0 and libswresample-dev binary packages
    - Do not compile with -Werror=format-security
    - Re-enable --disable-stripping
    - Revert soname change in ffmpeg Replaces due to moving presets back to ffmpeg
    - Update files to install
    - Update source package section in README.Debian
    - Update copyright file with regards to GPL vs LGPL
    - Remove obsolete get-orig-source.sh
    - Drop libdirac-dev dependency
    - Drop libxvidcore-dev dependency
    - Update list of optional dependencies
    - Only build the ffmpeg executables once
    - Update Maintainer field
    - Replace libavcodec53's Breaks on libavcodec-extra-53 with a Conflicts
    - Add dpkg (>= 1.15.6~) to Pre-Depends to ensure xz-compatibility

 -- Jon Severinsson <jon@severinsson.net>  Mon, 12 Nov 2012 12:00:00 +0100

libav (6:0.8.4-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New upstream security/bugfix release. New release fixes:
    (bug numbers reference http://bugzilla.libav.org, Closes: #688847)
    - h264 (Bug 118), vc1dec (CVE-2012-2796), sipr, bmpdec (bug 367), alsdec
      (CVE-2012-2775), rv34/rv40 (CVE-2012-2772), indeo3/indeo4
      (CVE-2012-2776, CVE-2012-2779, CVE-2012-2787, CVE-2012-2794,
      CVE-2012-2800), vorbisenc, vorbisdec (Bug 277), snow, ac3dec
      (CVE-2012-2802), avsdec (CVE-2012-2801), dfa (CVE-2012-2786,
      CVE-2012-2798), lagrith (CVE-2012-2793), wmaprodec (CVE-2012-2789 &
      Bug 327), avidec (CVE-2012-2788, CVE-2012-2790), cavsdec
      (CVE-2012-2777, CVE-2012-2784), wav (Bug 379), yuff4mpeg (Bug 373),
      mpegaudio, tiffenc, smacker (Bug 265).
    - smaller bug fixes in avconv (Bug 352)
    - fix lt() and lte() in function evaluator
    - fix segfault in avformat_open_input()
    - fix segfault in golomb decoder (bug 310)
    - fix segfault (double free) in libavfilter
    - convert dfa decoder to bytestream2 API to protect from overreads
    - bugfix in vf_pad/scale filter (Bug 203 & 245)
    - lavc: remove stats_out and stats_in from the options table.
      (Bug 380, Closes: #690726)
  * Drop patches applied upstream.

 -- Reinhard Tartler <siretart@tauware.de>  Mon, 22 Oct 2012 20:57:08 +0200

